<Document>

  <ColorBox Color="#FFFFFF" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="25" NOTES="Divider" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#FFFFFF" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Center"/>
  <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" NOTES="Metashield Rules" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#01b38a" OutlineThickness="4" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">

    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
      <ColorBox Color="#01b38a" NOTES="Header" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#01b38a" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
        <Box Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
          <Box Margin="8" Orientation="Vertical"/>
          <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Center">
            [color=#000000][head=2]Section IV: Metashield[/head][/color]
          </Box>
        </Box>
      </ColorBox>

      <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="10" NOTES="Body" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">

        This section describes what is commonly known in-character knowledge.

        <Table Columns="1" NOTES="Rule List">

          <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#154929" OutlineThickness="3" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
            <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
              <ColorBox Color="#154929" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#154929" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box Margin="20"/>
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                  [color=#68de8d][head=3]Never Shielded[/head][/color]
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#1B1B1E" OutlineThickness="10" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="10" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
                  99.99% of characters/players know these facts.
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical">
                <ColorBox Color="#154929" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#154929" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#152618" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#152618" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#154929]•[/color] The fact that Vermist Dust Sector is a highly dangerous place to be.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>
              </Box>

            </Box>
          </ColorBox>

          <ColorBox Color="#01b38a" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="15" NOTES="Divider" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#01b38a" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Center"/>

          <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#084647" OutlineThickness="3" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
            <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
              <ColorBox Color="#084647" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#084647" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                  [color=#1bc4dd][head=3]Opt In[/head][/color]
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#1B1B1E" OutlineThickness="10" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="10" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
                  A super-imposition percentage of characters/players know these facts.
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical">
                <ColorBox Color="#084647" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#084647" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#142826" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#142826" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#084647]•[/color] The fact that VD-Command (central command) is a fairly separate entity from Nanotrasen as a whole, due to distance; lack of Nanotrasen communication, and who knows what.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>

                <ColorBox Color="#084647" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#084647" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#273c39" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#273c39" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#084647]•[/color] That VDS consistently goes through anomalous/paranormal events.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>
              </Box>
            </Box>
          </ColorBox>

          <ColorBox Color="#01b38a" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="15" NOTES="Divider" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#01b38a" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Center"/>

          <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#555a05" OutlineThickness="3" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
            <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
              <ColorBox Color="#555a05" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#555a05" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                  [color=#eeee74][head=3]Sometimes Shielded[/head][/color]
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#1B1B1E" OutlineThickness="10" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="10" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
                  You need solid in-game evidence during the current round in order to even consider things on this list as a possibility.

                  In general, if it's protection for another player or their role, play in the space and don't meta-game or power-game them because you have out-of-character knowledge!
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical">
                <ColorBox Color="#555a05" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#555a05" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#2f2e0f" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#2f2e0f" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#555a05]•[/color] The idea that rival Nanotrasen organizations such as the Syndicate would even care or know about VDS, let alone send anyone on a mission here.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>

                <ColorBox Color="#555a05" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#555a05" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#423f25" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#423f25" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#555a05]•[/color] Certain technologies and abilities, such as chameleon items, magic, traitor implants, uplinks, things meant to be 'stealthy' or 'rare'.

                      If it would be more fun for the round if you played dumb, do it. Command/Security have more leeway when it comes to things like traitor items, but only with solid evidence or having no other possible explanation.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>
              </Box>
            </Box>
          </ColorBox>

          <ColorBox Color="#01b38a" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="15" NOTES="Divider" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#01b38a" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Center"/>

          <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#4b040e" OutlineThickness="3" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
            <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
              <ColorBox Color="#4b040e" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#4b040e" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center">
                  [color=#ec2149][head=3]Always Shielded[/head][/color]
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <ColorBox Color="#1B1B1E" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#1B1B1E" OutlineThickness="10" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                <Box HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="10" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Bottom">
                  Acknowledging, using, or being influenced by any information here in-character is considered meta-gaming.
                </Box>
              </ColorBox>

              <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical">
                <ColorBox Color="#4b040e" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#4b040e" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#300b12" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#300b12" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#4b040e]•[/color] Anything from your old life, should you respawn as a new character or ghost role.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>

                <ColorBox Color="#4b040e" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#4b040e" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#411721" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#411721" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#4b040e]•[/color] Anything you may have seen/heard/smelled as a ghost, while asleep, in hard-crit, etc.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>

                <ColorBox Color="#4b040e" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#4b040e" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                  <ColorBox Color="#300b12" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#300b12" OutlineThickness="5" VerticalAlignment="Top">
                    <Box HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="2" Orientation="Vertical" VerticalAlignment="Stretch">
                      [color=#4b040e]•[/color] Advantagous/metagamey LOOC/OOC/Discord chat information.

                      If somebody in LOOC says "hey how do i open my uplink?", don't start treating them like a traitor. If somebody over OOC asks "how do I start the engine?", don't immediately rush over if they're wanting on-hands help. Encourage them to reach out in-character.

                      Exceptions include LOOC/OOC check-ins, like somebody asking you to stop something because it's making them uncomfortable. You should obviously alter your character's behaviour then.
                    </Box>
                  </ColorBox>
                </ColorBox>
              </Box>
            </Box>
          </ColorBox>
        </Table>

      </Box>
    </Box>
  </ColorBox>

  <ColorBox Color="#FFFFFF" HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Margin="25" NOTES="Divider" Orientation="Vertical" OutlineColor="#FFFFFF" OutlineThickness="1" VerticalAlignment="Center"/>

</Document>
